  "slug": "how-to-make-cornbread",
  "name": "How to Make Cornbread for Beginners",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "An important factor in learning how to make cornbread is mixing the batter the right way. Cornbread batter doesn\u2019t need a lot of mixing. If you over-mix ingredients, you might end up with an unpleasant result. To make cornbread, you need:",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "In one bowl, combine the dry ingredients: corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt. In another separate bowl, combine the wet ingredients: sugar, honey, half and half, butter and eggs."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Pour the wet mixture into the dry, flour mixture. Mix only until the flour is moist, not more than 15 seconds. The resulting batter should be moist and lumpy."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Pour the batter into a greased baking pan. Bake at 400 F for half an hour or until you can insert a chopstick or toothpick in the cornbread and it comes out clean. Serve."
    }
  ],
  "servings": 4,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 30,
